    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1927-06-15T16:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1927-06-15T16:00:00-05:00" n="64"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d64">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">838.00/2326: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in Haiti</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gross</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1927-06-15T17:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 15, 1927—5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>29. General Russell’s despatch 1018, June 1, 1927. The Department hopes that no
                    further action will be taken looking to the enactment <pb facs="0153" n="51"
                        xml:id="pg_51"/> of the proposed amendments to the Constitution until the
                    Department has had an opportunity to express its opinion. Please inform
                    President Borno accordingly and request that the matter be held in abeyance.
                    Department will give you detailed instructions in the near future.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
